</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EC7B7C83DBE601A8E8EF5D7273761952" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="specimens seen">
<paragraph id="D08EEC64AB2EE04FCE129E9770BB6FF3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Specimens seen.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D5F431213223B4575AC8A1AAD6619072" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="DBA60F33D28DD3E5B9BCE0F2B33D95A3" bold="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">BRAZIL. Rio Grande do Sul</emphasis>
: Jaguari, ca. 12.5 km ao norte de Jaguari na BR-287 em 
<normalizedToken id="56521EB0A7C814F72071751FD94B9F59" originalValue="direção">direcao</normalizedToken>
a Santiago, fl., fr., Dec 2005, L.Y.S. Aona &amp; M.C. Machado 958 (UEC 3ex); loc. cit., gruta linha 1, fl., fr., 27 Dec 1985, J.N.C. Marchiori 149 (HDCF).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C2A2FFB5384D77EA35116E9D295C961C" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B25A09334969BD1D1000BA2B61FEC06B" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="969AAF3EC1078234360825D5D995B080" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="9DB6F6869B19FE882F8947026E0CA2CB" class="Liliopsida" family="Commelinaceae" genus="Tradescantia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tradescantia valida" order="Commelinales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="valida">
<emphasis id="1F32A20405E776A318FB1FE0DA4EED4A" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Tradescantia valida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to Brazil, more precisely to the state of Rio Grande do Sul (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0C1D4E84EDC3D307B6D1C2B03237973A" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Distribution map of studied Tradescantia L. in the South American domains. Full squares - T. crassula; White squares - T. chrysophylla; Triangles - T. valida; Circles - T. ambigua; Stars - T. boliviana. Light green- Amazon Forest; Orange- Cerrado; Red- Caatinga; Yellow- Chaco and Pantanal; Olive-green- Pampa; Dark green- Atlantic Forest; Purple- Andean Yungas." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.80.12232.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/133214" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">8</figureCitation>
). It can be found growing as rupicolous, rarely as a terrestrial, in rocky walls.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5BB826ABAC9D1A3390C52714477A9606" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="phenology">
<paragraph id="B11E9F81ACFEAC5500780A2605111EB0" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="515A4E6132672BC1C9FB3EE1B5380678" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">It was found in bloom and fruit in December and April.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="61C546D64864D477D167D1A0236A5BAB" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="050300E3566A5504C3AE1CF767D7614F" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D6E9AEA8C10162D89399455F77D1180" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="6DCC554558B4E8AB1EAC9235631C4DDB" class="Liliopsida" family="Commelinaceae" genus="Tradescantia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tradescantia valida" order="Commelinales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="valida">
<emphasis id="63D49056CAC79A98DE78A42170550747" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Tradescantia valida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from the cultivated type collection and collections in Jaguari, state of Rio Grande do Sul. Thus, in accordance with the IUCN recommendations (
<bibRefCitation id="326CA6A43A6921C80FF39A1EC537D484" author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="IUCN Red List Unit, Cambridge" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/" refId="B25" refString="IUCN, 2001. The IUCN red list of threatened species, version 2010.4. IUCN Red List Unit, Cambridge, http://www.iucnredlist.org/" title="The IUCN red list of threatened species, version 2010.4" url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/" year="2001">IUCN 2001</bibRefCitation>
), it should be considered as Data Deficient (DD), until further information on the species becomes available.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="778907D16C083F473CE3A15FD3242B40" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B7B85D6D7A69B79C569ED693E33BBE4C" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="91D224B9F03BAA8A90A9F97B175CE5E0" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="CC7D68B468E3DE79D43A6AA9FADFDFC7" class="Liliopsida" family="Commelinaceae" genus="Tradescantia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tradescantia valida" order="Commelinales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="valida">
<emphasis id="C9CEBC6535D30CB856FA506BA9583180" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Tradescantia valida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to the remaining three species in the 
<taxonomicName id="EDC1C3F2E6B20C93E9587C5E9914AF0C" genus="T." lsidName="T. crassula" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species" species="crassula">
<emphasis id="DCCE58DE90B1B193685C849833C89C7A" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. crassula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, due to its erect habit, definite base, sessile, conduplicate to falcate, succulent leaves, generally with inconspicuous secondary veins, cincinni bracts non-saccate at base, pistil longer than the stamens, hilum longer than 
<normalizedToken id="AE9C803C006CEBC6EDD198205C98FC30" originalValue="½">1/2</normalizedToken>
the length of the seed, and for preferentially inhabiting open areas and rocky outcrops (
<bibRefCitation id="3E9852CD50551EA26076202215D23790" DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" author="Pellegrini, MOO" journalOrPublisher="Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refId="B29" refString="Pellegrini, MOO, 2015. Filogenia e revisao taxonomica de Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D.R.Hunt (Commelinaceae). In: MsC thesis. Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, DOI: https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" title="Filogenia e revisao taxonomica de Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D. R. Hunt (Commelinaceae)" url="https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" volumeTitle="MsC thesis." year="2015">Pellegrini 2015</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5E7EF9DE4E958EA0E0F238B6CED38294" author="Pellegrini, MOO" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="79 - 84" refId="B30" refString="Pellegrini, MOO, 2016. A new species of Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D.R.Hunt (Commelinaceae) from Southern Brazil. Phytotaxa 265 (1): 79 - 84" title="A new species of Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D. R. Hunt (Commelinaceae) from Southern Brazil." volume="265" year="2016">2016</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="F0E4496C20A501614A87D5E8641D9231" class="Liliopsida" family="Commelinaceae" genus="Tradescantia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tradescantia valida" order="Commelinales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="valida">
<emphasis id="B459C70B289C337A35A5A5B0EB10B246" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Tradescantia valida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated easily from all remaining species of the 
<taxonomicName id="9279531BF8CBB8951B14319277411C71" genus="T." lsidName="T. crassula" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species" species="crassula">
<emphasis id="5D4D06C65BAB67542B0C0F389E16E243" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. crassula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by its spathaceous cincinni bracts and by the presence of supernumerary bracts. The presence of spathaceous cincinni bracts is a character previously reported in 
<taxonomicName id="7DE34717177771F6B35A792CBBABDF31" genus="T." lsidName="T. subsp. sect." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="section" section="Austrotradescentia" species="crassula" subSpecies="sect.">T. sect. Austrotradescentia</taxonomicName>
exclusively for 
<taxonomicName id="EF489A225CD750D2F13595B3EF68EC57" genus="T." lsidName="T. umbraculifera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species" species="umbraculifera">
<emphasis id="363465706FCA7764DAF951FC34CC22AC" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. umbraculifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hand.-Mazz., a member of a clade named 
<taxonomicName id="14F6705351145DC23C22D7D0D27D20A8" genus="T." lsidName="T. fluminensis" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species" species="fluminensis">
<emphasis id="90F0126528C317B6A336257EB4EEB875" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. fluminensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by 
<bibRefCitation id="33138C79BAD0EFF1BB10FA59A416B2F0" DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" author="Pellegrini, MOO" journalOrPublisher="Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refId="B29" refString="Pellegrini, MOO, 2015. Filogenia e revisao taxonomica de Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D.R.Hunt (Commelinaceae). In: MsC thesis. Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, DOI: https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" title="Filogenia e revisao taxonomica de Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D. R. Hunt (Commelinaceae)" url="https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" volumeTitle="MsC thesis." year="2015">Pellegrini (2015)</bibRefCitation>
, and thus quite remarkable in this distantly related species. Aside from that, the presence of supernumerary bracts is unique within 
<taxonomicName id="1AC8AE99A8B8947AB669D3C5C3BBA311" genus="T." lsidName="T. subsp. sect." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="section" section="Austrotradescantia" species="fluminensis" subSpecies="sect.">T. sect. Austrotradescantia</taxonomicName>
, but well-known in species from 
<taxonomicName id="D35F8E0BEEE575067729617CE1EA389A" genus="T." lsidName="T. subsp. sect." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="section" section="Cymbispatha" species="fluminensis" subSpecies="sect.">T. sect. Cymbispatha</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="43A1CD796CF63111922FE9E1749AEA47" DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" author="Pellegrini, MOO" journalOrPublisher="Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refId="B29" refString="Pellegrini, MOO, 2015. Filogenia e revisao taxonomica de Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D.R.Hunt (Commelinaceae). In: MsC thesis. Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, DOI: https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" title="Filogenia e revisao taxonomica de Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D. R. Hunt (Commelinaceae)" url="https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" volumeTitle="MsC thesis." year="2015">Pellegrini 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="CD21AEA21005490558130243AA315ED8" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364416X694053" author="Pellegrini, MOO" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="950 - 958" refId="B33" refString="Pellegrini, MOO, Forzza, RC, Sakuragui, CM, 2016. (Con)Fused bracts: The identity and application of Tradescantia cymbispatha C.B.Clarke (Commelinaceae) and a neglected new Tradescantia species from Bolivia. Systematic Botany 41 (4): 950 - 958, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1600/036364416X694053" title="(Con) Fused bracts: The identity and application of Tradescantia cymbispatha C. B. Clarke (Commelinaceae) and a neglected new Tradescantia species from Bolivia." url="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364416X694053" volume="41" year="2016">Pellegrini et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="13E0402FB7CB99C5FB46D1323E8C14E6" genus="T." lsidName="T. subsp. sect." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="section" section="Mandonia" species="fluminensis" subSpecies="sect.">T. sect. Mandonia</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="C4F620EE1144C07EC339039C8BC4CFBD" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/3393009" author="Grant, JR" journalOrPublisher="Novon" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="117 - 123" refId="B12" refString="Grant, JR, 2000. New Mesoamerican species of Dichorisandra and Tradescantia section Mandonia (Commelinaceae). Novon 10 (2): 117 - 123, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/3393009" title="New Mesoamerican species of Dichorisandra and Tradescantia section Mandonia (Commelinaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/3393009" volume="10" year="2000">Grant 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="446C61E1E22FEC45A3EE1E10CB55026A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" author="Pellegrini, MOO" journalOrPublisher="Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refId="B29" refString="Pellegrini, MOO, 2015. Filogenia e revisao taxonomica de Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D.R.Hunt (Commelinaceae). In: MsC thesis. Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, DOI: https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" title="Filogenia e revisao taxonomica de Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D. R. Hunt (Commelinaceae)" url="https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" volumeTitle="MsC thesis." year="2015">Pellegrini 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C4B1F77A6604960BFF3ECE91D6F4D365" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
In the 
<taxonomicName id="6AA33A9BC687DB636BD73DB1064EE404" genus="T." lsidName="T. crassula" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species" species="crassula">
<emphasis id="73BCC5ADC67BC03FE676BCBFDF2EDE30" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. crassula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, 
<taxonomicName id="35F61A994345BB4AA4030FA684AD5D3B" genus="T." lsidName="T. valida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species" species="valida">
<emphasis id="D3CC51E34445B3399A00910C9AE08E8E" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. valida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="1567B7110BF884FB9383818FE047DD83" genus="T." lsidName="T. cerinthoides" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species" species="cerinthoides">
<emphasis id="D77F20B3358E47CBD4186968AE916417" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. cerinthoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to its sepals without dorsal keels. However, they can be easily differentiated due to its generally linear elliptic to linear lanceolate to lanceolate leaf-blades (
<emphasis id="AD3AC82AD85DB7BA9093775A9110074D" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">vs.</emphasis>
elliptic to broadly elliptic or ovate to broadly ovate or obovate to broadly obovate, in 
<taxonomicName id="CB81FBCBF28317B959EB252D4291B899" genus="T." lsidName="T. cerinthoides" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species" species="cerinthoides">
<emphasis id="30416A83D3A340CF5B93FD9265474CD8" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. cerinthoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), glabrous with margins setose at the base or until the middle (
<emphasis id="03197C4A9A963F434878970CDB7CAD4D" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">vs.</emphasis>
pubescent on both sides or only abaxially, rarely glabrous on both sides with ciliate margins), and pedicels and sepals glabrous or only sparsely pubescent with eglandular hairs (
<emphasis id="62D08A9369C3DDD50A8CE5101CCC5A11" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">vs.</emphasis>
evenly densely velutine to hispid, sometimes with a mixture of glandular and eglandular hairs). 
<taxonomicName id="29F5EC1DC107895BE58D4D9351BAB58A" class="Liliopsida" family="Commelinaceae" genus="Tradescantia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tradescantia valida" order="Commelinales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="valida">
<emphasis id="38E65016A9EFBAFB210640B6C68EB9DE" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Tradescantia valida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is much more similar to 
<taxonomicName id="6BEDF76B2ECC6532EB369C1DF9760F49" genus="T." lsidName="T. crassula" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species" species="crassula">
<emphasis id="C815C1DDDAE6633318D3729E5E1E5542" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. crassula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CB3EEC954BF0C067D53C45980D634B16" genus="T." lsidName="T. seubertiana" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species" species="seubertiana">
<emphasis id="24C3E87A3EA566AAA25C106D9DC3532A" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. seubertiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
M.Pell., due to their leaf-blades and floral pubescence. These species can be easily differentiated by the pubescence of the margin of their leaf-sheaths (ciliate to shortly-setose in 
<taxonomicName id="F4A59F1B0C63EA76ABE1E93BFF0E7400" genus="T." lsidName="T. crassula" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species" species="crassula">
<emphasis id="7D73A63B632E6CD85553D3DFAFF7ED6B" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. crassula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; glabrous in 
<taxonomicName id="84EE2670E35E1EA6341050859C46398A" genus="T." lsidName="T. seubertiana" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species" species="seubertiana">
<emphasis id="4652499B85959DF3E9E02707503484D4" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. seubertiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and long-setose in 
<taxonomicName id="9722554509EC5562EEAAD128FBBA3CA0" genus="T." lsidName="T. valida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species" species="valida">
<emphasis id="3B27CD45D2484B0627BB1AF48D5170EA" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. valida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the pubescence of their sepals (long-setose along the keels in 
<taxonomicName id="53BD9DD32E69CA9728DAEBF0629C6191" genus="T." lsidName="T. crassula" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species" species="crassula">
<emphasis id="4247E525EE4CAB11C636FB6164EC349F" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. crassula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; glabrous in 
<taxonomicName id="00DFE3280D04B9099D68A8B1A345A70F" genus="T." lsidName="T. seubertiana" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species" species="seubertiana">
<emphasis id="B087586D49802D1ABD54FF5BB7C8980D" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. seubertiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and glabrous or with few hairs at the apex in 
<taxonomicName id="137EB76D7142CAB2270A2F2C74D60220" genus="T." lsidName="T. valida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species" species="valida">
<emphasis id="6E2C28A2B9E2DF5087DA96ED172D2731" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. valida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and by the shape of their floral buds (broadly ovoid 
<taxonomicName id="C1978730207FBE1903B41CFE43D8BF21" genus="T." lsidName="T. crassula" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species" species="crassula">
<emphasis id="7CDE05A5DFCF6B1FD660D5C8EB4D95A4" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. crassula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; ellipsoid in 
<taxonomicName id="956131B12D71C0AB28F01887FBE1E7BA" genus="T." lsidName="T. seubertiana" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species" species="seubertiana">
<emphasis id="5E9C8EBDD342264D33637AEF72A68756" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. seubertiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and ellipsoid in 
<taxonomicName id="817F8E2A34A7FE18292720D34A342DDA" genus="T." lsidName="T. valida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species" species="valida">
<emphasis id="DDABE0A09A1BB914185715601A623E46" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. valida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
